# Pandoc's --standalone man template tests at build time whether the output
# device has a real Courier ('C'/'CB') font family. Text devices (ascii/
# utf8/latin1) -- the only kind `man` uses in a terminal -- don't, so the
# probe itself, and one literal \f[C] used for indented code blocks, print
# "cannot select font" to stderr. Pandoc's own template comments say this is
# expected and already falls back to Bold for text devices; the rendered
# man page is unaffected either way. Harmless, upstream-known noise.
canlogger: groff-message
